PERTH (miningweekly.com) – Gold miner Northern Star has appointed Michael Chaney as nonexecutive chairperson, effective from July 1. Chaney is currently chairperson of ASX-listed Wesfarmers and was previously chairperson of the National Australia Bank and Woodside Petroleum. He holds Bachelor of Science and Master of Business Administration degrees and has worked as a petroleum geologist in Australia and the US. Chaney will replace Bill Beament, who will leave the Northern Star board on July 1. “I am delighted that Chaney has agreed to take on the role of chair of Northern Star. He is one of Australia’s most respected and successful business leaders whose vast knowledge and experience at the highest levels will be invaluable to the company as it embarks on its next chapter,” Beament said.